author: Laurie Burkitt
title: Carnival Corp. Doubles Lines in China
text:
SHANGHAI—Carnival Corp. is doubling its cruise lines in China, betting that tourism will grow even as the economy slows.
Carnival executives said in a media briefing Tuesday they plan to add two cruising brands—the company’s namesake Carnival brand and its upscale Aida line—to China by 2017, in addition to the Princess and Costa services currently used in the country. By next year, the company will operate six cruise ships in China,...
